Mini HTTP Server in C++

A simple educational HTTP server built in C++ using TCP sockets.
This project was created to learn low-level networking, HTTP basics, and clean C++ project structure.

Features

    TCP socket server
    Runs on localhost:8080
    Handles HTTP GET requests
    Parses HTTP request line

    Simple routing :
        / → home page
        /about → about page
        /time → current server time
    Returns proper HTTP responses
    Handles 404 Not Found
    Serves static HTML files

Tech Stack :
    C++
    TCP sockets
    Linux / macOS compatible
    Makefile build system

Project Structure :
    src/        # source files
    include/    # header files
    public/     # static HTML files
    docs/       # extra documentation
    Build
    make
    Run
    ./server

Then open:
    http://localhost:8080

Test with curl :
    curl http://localhost:8080/
    curl http://localhost:8080/about
    curl http://localhost:8080/time
    curl http://localhost:8080/unknown

Learning Goals :

    Understand TCP socket programming
    Learn how HTTP requests and responses work
    Practice modular C++ code organization
    Work collaboratively with Git and GitHub

Possible Improvements :
    Support more HTTP methods
    Better request parsing
    MIME type detection
    Serve CSS and JavaScript files
    Add logging
    Add unit tests
    Handle multiple clients
    Use threads or select()

